result.execSummary:
The defendant Montez I Thompson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Robbery with Threat of Force, PTAC [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Montez I Thompson in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel, Chariey M., and defendant. 

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  66  months, consecutive to any other sentence,  with 189 days credit -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  24 months   -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  42  months.

Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 
- Restitution is set at $0 (zero)

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
- No violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause
- Follow all rules of extended supervision
- AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment
- Successfully complete a Parenting/Fatherhood class
- Obtain GED/HSD
- Seek/Maintain full-time employment or a combination of part-time employment and school
- No Contact with the co-actors - Joshua Brooks  and/or  Gerald Gillie
- Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis 
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Pretrial Incarceration Credit, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court involved in a Jury Trial.  Matter adjourned for sentencing.  Parties informed that effective December 14, 2015, this matter will be assigned to Br. 28, Judge Sanders in Room 629 of the Courthouse.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 17, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to the amended charge.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Montez I Thompson in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Original Amended Information received and filed.  Defense acknowledges receipt of the Amended Information, waives reading and enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of his client.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Carpenter in Court today indicated that the currently scheduled Speedy Trial date of October 5, 2015 needs to be adjourned as he is not available.  ADA Michael Lonski in Court and does not oppose the rescheduling of the Jury Trial.  Matter adjourned to October 19, 2015 for Jury Trial.  This new date complies with the Speedy Trial Demand.
Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter in court.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Final pretrial conducted.  Matter to remain calendared for Jury Trial on October 5, 2015.

Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter in court, defendant Montez I Thompson not in court, in custody.   Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter set for Jury Trial and Final Pretrial.  Later same morning, it came to the Court's addition of the correspondence submitted by the defendant which requested a Speedy Jury Demand.  The previously set dates with Attorney Carpenter is outside the speedy demand time limits.  Attorney Carpenter had left and is not aware of the new court dates for Final Pretrial and Jury Trial.  Correspondence sent to Attorney Carpenter notifying him of this situation and supplying Attorney Carpenter with the new final pretrial and jury trial date.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 25, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Letter from defendant.  Copy forwarded to Jeff Carpenter and State.

Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter in court, defendant Montez I Thompson not in court, in custody.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense motion for modification of bail proceeded.  Court sets bails in the amount of $2,000.00 cash with the same previous conditions of bail.  Plea hearing scheduled for August 12, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter in court, defendant Montez I Thompson not in court, in custody.  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for scheduling and bail hearing, however defense counsel was not able to make a timely appearance at the scheduled time of 8:30am, and now in the afternoon Branch 21 is in jury trial, case adjourned.  Case remains calendared in Branch 21.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for July 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Montez I Thompson in custody.  Antonella Aleman for Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed.  Court found probable cause and bound Defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Brash, Branch 21.   Original Information received and filed.  Copy given to Defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant was arraigned in open court and pled not guilty. Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 21.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 6, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for July 6, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Taco Bell located at 1940 S. 14th Street, Auto Zone located at 1802 W. Forest Home, Gerald G. and Joshua B.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms. Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Montez I Thompson in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Montez I Thompson in custody.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bvj
